 This install applies to "Cannonfodder 2" © 1994 Sensible Software.
 The english, french and the german version is supported.
 
 This install requires WHDLoad to be in the path. It can be found in the
 WHDLoad package.
 To install from a different drive than DF0: select Expert Mode during
 installation.

 The installed program requires 1 MB ChipMem and 0.5 MB OtherMem.
 It can be quit by pressing F10 (key can be changed with Tooltype "QuitKey=").

 If you have problems with this installation please try and get a newer
 version of this package from the WHDLoad WWW-Page. If that doesn't help try
 some Tooltypes like NOCACHE, NOAUTOVEC, NOVBRMOVE, NOMMU, PAL or NTSC. If
 that also fails, please inform the author via the Bug-Report-Form which
 can be accessed on the WHDLoad WWW-Page.

 For the full WHDLoad package, other installs and updates refer to:
	http://www.whdload.de/
 or	aminet:dev/misc/whdload#?
 and	aminet:game/patch/

 previous versions created by Wepl in May 1996, January and September 1998.

 version 1.5 (03.06.00) done by Wepl:
 - reworked and cleanup

 version 1.6 (10.01.01) done by Wepl:
 - accesses to AGA registers removed
 - bplcon0.color fixed

 version 1.7 (20.02.01) done by Wepl:
 - two access faults removed

 version 1.8 (20.07.03) done by Wepl:
 - keyboard handling fixed (thx to Seppo Seppala for report)

 version 1.9 (12.08.05) done by Wepl:
 - support for french version added (thanks to Denis Lechevalier)
 - two exotica icons added

 version 1.10 (08.09.05) done by Wepl:
 - load/save fixed for french version

 version 1.11 (19.05.09) done by Wepl:
 - fixed for WHDLoad version 16.9 (illegal chars in directory name)
 - to migrate from a previous version you need to move the 'save'
   directory into the 'data' directory
 - save buffer moved to fastmem, because of this now requires at least
   WHDLoad version 16.9
 - new install script

 version 1.12 (17.05.11) done by Wepl:
 - keyboard handling problems on some machines (68040) fixed, issue #2422
 - access fault on loading a savegame after playing and less than 4 savegames
   exist fixed, issue #2438

 version 1.13 (07.03.26) done by Wepl / Arise from Decay
 - trainer for all versions added
 - support for italian version added (issue #3896)
 - source at https://github.com/wepl/winstalls

